The paper focuses on explaining the decisions made by deep neural networks in image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The methodology proposed in the paper involves utilizing the structure of the network and backpropagating explanations, which are common techniques used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of nonlinear methods such as deep neural networks, which is a topic covered in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in natural language processing, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
